   <h4>Let’s Recap Part-Part Relationships</h4>
   <p>In <b>part-part relationships</b>, the digit in the denominator indicates the number of items that are in one
      part of the set, and the digit in the numerator indicates the number of items that are in the other part of
      the set. The fractional unit, or number of equi-partitions of the whole, is determined by adding the digits
      in the numerator and denominator together. For example,
   </p>
   <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
         <p>The number of fruit in this set that are pears is <abbr title=""><sup>3</sup>⁄<sub>6</sub></abbr> the number of fruit that are not pears.</p>
